<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Purple2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Purple,</orth> adj. 1) of the colour of the violet: <emph>the p. pride which on thy</emph> (the violet's) <cit><quote>soft cheek for complexion dwells,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 99.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 99, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the p. violets,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 4.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 1, 16</bibl></cit>. <emph>before milk-white, now p. with love's wound</emph> (the viola tricolor) <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 102</bibl>. <cit><quote>p. grapes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.170" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 170</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. the sails,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 198</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 1168" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1168</bibl>.<lb />2) red; used of blood: <cit><quote>p. tears that his wound wept,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1054" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1054</bibl></cit>. <emph>the p. fountain</emph> (of her wound) <bibl n="shak. luc 1734" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1734</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.94" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.99" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.64" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 6, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.277" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 277</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 92</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>